						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall of the Bhairava shrine in the Vālīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Alluntikkaraiśaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Gaṇḍagōpāla. Year 4: 1255 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The details of date, <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi>, Makara 25, ba. 8, Sunday, Viśākha corresponds to 1255 A.D. January 3, Sunday, f.d.n. ·59.</p>						

						<p>This incomplete inscription stops after mentioning Niṉṟaiyūr-nāḍu, a district in Kuṉṟavattana-kōṭṭam, a subdivision of Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-maṇḍalam.</p>						

						</summary>
